ts-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-297x197.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-800x530.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-768x509.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-1536x1018.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-2048x1357.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-696x461.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-1068x708.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-1920x1272.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-lighting-system-634x420.jpg 634w\"></a></p><p>While most Nutcase helmets are noticed for their colors and patterns, the VIO begs to be noticed thanks to its integrated LED lights. From the front, to the sides, and the back, the VIO offers near 360º lighting with white, amber, and red LEDs. Up front, the head badge doubles as a 200 lumen headlight, while the rear and side LEDs are 65 lumen. A single button at the back of the helmet controls all three lights, with 3 different lighting modes – all three steady, headlight steady and side/rear flashing, and headlight steady and side/rear pulsing. Charging is said to take two hours, which provides a three hour run time.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-7.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-7.jpg\" alt=\"Nutcase VIO helmet recharging\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-7.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-7.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-7-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-7-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-7-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumo