021-10-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Sold in two shell sizes, the VIO is offered in a&nbsp;S/M (55- 59cm) and L/XL (59- 62cm). Both of those can be adjusted with their spin dial retention system. For an added premium touch, the helmets include Fidlock magnetic buckles on the chin strap and locking strap dividers.</p><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6.jpg\" alt=\"Nutcase VIO helmet visor\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-630x420.jpg 630w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-800x533.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-768x512.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-696x464.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-1068x712.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weight-2021-6-630x420.jpg 630w\"></a></p><p>Riders that prefer the look of a visor can snap on the included plastic brim up front. The pegs are fairly difficult to get seated, but once they finally snap into place, they seem to hold well.</p><h2>Actual Weights</h2><p><a href=\"https://bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights.jpg\" alt=\"Nutcase VIO helmet actual weights\" width=\"2415\" height=\"1600\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2415px) 100vw, 2415px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb8 src ng ngcb8 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights.jpg\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights.jpg 2415w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-297x197.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-800x530.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-768x509.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-1536x1018.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-2048x1357.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-696x461.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-1068x708.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-1920x1272.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-634x420.jpg 634w\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights.jpg 2415w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-297x197.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-800x530.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-768x509.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-1536x1018.jpg 1536w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-2048x1357.jpg 2048w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-696x461.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-1068x708.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-1920x1272.jpg 1920w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/bikerumor-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/02/Nutcase-Vio-Mips-helmet-with-integrated-lights-review-actual-weights-634x420.jpg 634w\"></a></p><p>On the scale, the S/M helmet checked in at 429g, while the L/XL was 461g, with an additional 18g for the visor. That’s not super light in the world of helmets without lights, but for a helmet with multiple lights, MIPS, and a visor, it’s impressive.</p><h2>First Impressions</h2><p>Nutcase really shot for the moon with the VIO and it shows. Nearly every aspect of this helmet seems well thought out and offers a premium feel at an attainable price point of $149.95. Like other helmets with only two shell sizes though, the fit will work better for some riders than others. I find myself right in the middle of the two sizes with the S/M tight at the temples, where the L/XL just feels a little big. However, I still fit within the adjustment range of the retention system and the larger helmet provides ample room for winter headgear, which has been helpful with recent testing. I’d say that the fit profile will be better for those with more round head shapes, than oval.</p><p>Overall, the VIO feels very well ventilated with the three huge vents in the front of the helmet swallowing large volumes of air. I haven’t had the chance to test out the helmet in truly hot conditions, so I can’t speak to that, but my first impression is that this should be a comfortable helmet year ’round.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-large-leaderboard-2\"></span></p><p>On one hand, the VIO is yet another thing you’l have to plug in and charge for your ride, but in this case, you’re charging one device instead of three different lights. Combine that with the fact that they’re integrated into the helmet making it impossible to forget them for your next ride, and you have a very intriguing helmet from Nutcase that seems perfect for anyone looking to increase their visibility with a safe, comfortable helmet.<span data-ez-name=\"bikerumor_com-leader-1\"></span></p><p><a href=\"https://nutcasehelmets.com/collections/vio\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>nutcasehelmets.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b3c87aa69e48d50cb584de238ab598bf8bb738bc7d7eb1192f4b2fe530067716","category":"Cycling"}